comments: Tate (HOU) momentarily brings his hand to Haliburton's (IND) side and the contact during the drive is marginal.
Smith Jr. (HOU) maintains a legal defensive position and absorbs the contact initiated by Turner (IND) during the layup attempt at the basket.
Turner (IND) delivers body contact to Tate (HOU) that affects his driving shot attempt at the basket.
Green (HOU) and Smith (IND) make simultaneous contact with the ball and deflect it away. The arm contact after the deflection is incidental.
Tate (HOU) slides his hand off of Nembhard's (IND) back as he goes to the ground and the contact is marginal.
Nembhard (IND) firms up in Tate's (POR) path and marginal contact occurs as they come together during the pick. Tate proceeds to go to the ground, but was not dislodged from his defensive position.
Green (HOU) lowers his hand down and makes contact with the ball and part of Haliburton's (IND) hand that is on the ball, which dislodges it during the driving shot attempt.
Nembhard (IN)D lightly brushes Tate's (HOU) arm and marginal contact occurs during the pass in transition.
Hield (IND) brings his hand to the ball and cleanly deflects it away from Martin Jr. (HOU).

Haliburton IND) receives the pass and his right heel is on the half-court line. Haliburton has not fully established himself or the ball in the frontcourt and is able to continue dribbling in the backcourt,.
